usage: monci [\-h] [\-\-version] [\-v] [\-\-debug]
.IP
{ci,lint,query\-source,image,bootstrap,update,remove,dedup,images,distros,shell,run} ...
.PP
CI tool
.SS "positional arguments:"
.TP
{ci,lint,query\-source,image,bootstrap,update,remove,dedup,images,distros,shell,run}
sub\-command help
.TP
ci
clone a git repository and launch a container instance
in the
.TP
lint
Run consistency checks on a source directory using all
available build
.TP
query\-source
Query informations about a source
.TP
image
image creation and maintenance
.TP
bootstrap
Create or update the whole set of OS images for the CI
.TP
update
Update existing OS images
.TP
remove
Remove existing OS images
.TP
dedup
Deduplicate disk usage in image directories
.TP
images
List OS images
.TP
distros
List OS images
.TP
shell
Run a shell in the given container
.TP
run
Run a shell in the given container
.SS "options:"
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
show this help message and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
show program's version number and exit
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
verbose output
.TP
\fB\-\-debug\fR
debugging output
.SH  CI  SUBCOMMAND

usage: monci ci [\-h] [\-v] [\-\-debug] [\-I IMAGEDIR] [\-C CONFIG]
.IP
[\-\-extra\-packages\-dir EXTRA_PACKAGES_DIR] [\-\-branch BRANCH]
[\-s SOURCE_TYPE] [\-B file.yaml] [\-a dir] [\-\-source\-only]
[\-\-shell] [\-\-linger] [\-\-option OPTION] [\-\-quick]
image [source]
.SS "positional arguments:"
.TP
image
name of the image used to build
.TP
source
path or url of the repository or source package to
build. Default: the current directory
.SS "options:"
.TP
