show this help message and exit
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
verbose output
.TP
\fB\-\-debug\fR
debugging output
.TP
\fB\-I\fR, \fB\-\-imagedir\fR IMAGEDIR
path to the directory that contains container images.
Default: from configuration file, or \fI\,/var/lib/machines\/\fP
.TP
\fB\-C\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR CONFIG
path to the Moncic\-CI config file to use. By default,
look in a number of well\-known locations, see
https://github.com/ARPA\-SIMC/moncicci/blob/main/doc/moncic\-ci\-config.md
.TP
\fB\-\-extra\-packages\-dir\fR EXTRA_PACKAGES_DIR
directory where extra packages, if present, are added
to package sources in containers
.TP
\fB\-\-branch\fR BRANCH
branch to be used. Default: let 'git clone' choose
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-source\-type\fR SOURCE_TYPE
name of the procedure used to run the CI. Use 'list'
to list available options. Default: autodetect
.TP
\fB\-B\fR, \fB\-\-build\-config\fR file.yaml
YAML file with build configuration
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-artifacts\fR dir
directory where build artifacts will be stored
.TP
\fB\-\-source\-only\fR
only build source packages
.TP
\fB\-\-shell\fR
